Mr. Sunday Ogunniyi, the Special Assistant on Environmental Services to the Kwara State Governor, Abdulfatah Ahmed has resigned his appointment. Ogunniyi’s resignation letter to the governor tendered through the office of the Secretary to the Kwara State Government did not state the reason behind his decision. A copy of the letter sighted by newsmen on Wednesday reads: “With humility sir, I wish to inform you of my intention to resign my political appointment as Special Assistant on Environmental Services with effect from the date of this letter. “While wishing you a continued happy tenure, I am sincerely thanking you for the opportunity given me to serve.”  